<% if is_admin? %>
  <h1>Help page</h1>
  <div class="help-div">
    <h2>Navigation Bar</h2>
    <p><b>Manage Teams</b> - Allows you to create and delete teams</p>
    <p><b>Manage Users</b> - Allows you to create and delete users</p>
    <p><b>Feedback & Ratings</b> - Takes you to the Feedback & Rating page. Shows 
                                        Feedback on Team and associated ratings.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="help-div">
    <h2>Admin Code</h2>
    <p>The admin code is used to allow other professors to sign up with admin rights. To use, send the
    code to an admin, and instruct them to enter the code into the 'Team/admin code' field upon signup.</p>
    <p>In case the code is leaked, select 'Regenerate Code' to reset & regenerate the admin code. When this is done,
    the previous code will be invalidated.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="help-div">
    <h2>Steps to Reset User Password</h2>
    <p>1. From the home page, click on the "Manage Users" button.</p>
    <p>2. From the "Manage Users" page, click on the name of the user whose password needs to be reset.</p>
    <p>3. Click on the "Regenerate Password" button. </p>
    <p>4. You will be redirected back to the home page. At the top of the page, there will be confirmation that the user's password was reset. 
    For example, if the user's name is Adam, the text at the top of the page will be: "Adam's new password is: yKhGle4pQA". </p>
    <p>5. You can now copy and send the new password to the user through your preferred method of communication. </p>
  </div>

  <div class="help-div">
    <h2>Team Summary View </h2>
    <p><b>Urgency/Intervention Level</b> - This displays the overall urgency of the team's feedback and the necessary 
                                            intervention that is required from the instructor. <br>
      <ul>
        <li><u>Low</u> means that all members have categorized their feedback as "low". 
        The team is progressing well and instructor intervention is not needed at this time.</li>
        <li><u>Medium</u> means that at least one member on the team has categorized their feedback 
        as "medium", and no member has categorized their feedback as "high". 
        Instructor intervention is requested as time permits.</li>
        <li><u>High</u> means that at least one member on the team has categorized their feedback 
        as "high". Instructor intervention is required ASAP.</li>
        <li><u>No Feedback</u> means that not all team members have submitted their feedback for the week.
        This will automatically populate as "medium" after the due date has passed and not all team members 
        have submitted their feedback. Team members not submitting their feedback on time indicates the team needs some intervention.</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
    <p><b>Colour Coded System</b> - This reflects the team's overall urgency/intervention level. <br>
      <ul>
        <li>A <u>green</u> circle means that the average rating is >6 and the urgency is low, or if the average rating is >8 and the urgency is medium.</li>
        <li>A <u>yellow</u> circle means that the average rating is (6-8] and the urgency is medium.</li>
        <li>A <u>red</u> circle means that the average rating is <=6 or if the urgency is high.</li>
        <li>A <u>blank</u> circle means that not all team members have submitted their feedback for the week. 
        The circle will automatically turn yellow after the due date has passed and not all team members 
        have submitted their feedback. Team members not submitting their feedback on time indicates the 
        team needs some intervention.</li>
      </ul>
    <p><b>Average Rating (Out of 10)</b> - This rating reflects the team's overall health and is determined using team membersâ€™ responses to the feedback questions.</p>
    <p><b>Other Ratings </b> - These ratings are used to rate specific aspects of the team's health. Each specific rating is rated from a scale of 0 to 4.<br> 
    <p>0 - Strongly Disagree, 1 - Disagree, 2 - Neutral, 3 - Agree, 4 - Strongly Agree</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Everyone in the group is contributing equally.</li>
        <li>Everyone in the group is attending all meetings (unless they have an excused absence).</li>
        <li>The group treats me with respect and provides constructive criticism for my work when needed.</li>
        <li>My group members take the time to share their knowledge and assist other members of group when needed.</li>
      </ul>
    
    
    <p><b>Team Name</b> - The assigned name to the team.</p>
    <p><b>Team Code</b> - Provide this code to students prior to signup, and instruct them to enter the code into the 
      'Team/admin code' field upon signup so they are added to the appropriate team.</p>
    <p><b>Team Members</b> - List of team members.</p>
    <p><b>View Team Aggregated Feedback</b> - Show aggregated team feedback.</p>
    
  </div>
  <p><%= link_to 'Back', :back %></p>
<% end %>